    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Early form of footstool that was reproduced in great numbers during the 19th century. Thebes stools generally have concave tops, with flared legs and cross bracing. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052022/Cooper, Put Your Feet Up, Old House Interiors (2003)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>早期的一種腳凳，於西元十九世紀時大量複製生產。底比斯凳的凳座表面一般為下凹弧面，凳腿外翹，且凳座下有十字交叉的撐條。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Frühe Form eines Fußschemels, der während des 19. Jahrhunderts in großer Stückzahl wieder gebaut wurde. Der Theben-Hocker hat im Allgemeinen eine konkave Sitzfläche mit ausgestellten Beinen und Kreuzverstrebungen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
